# On-Prem / Offline Environment

This project runs in an air-gapped, on-premises environment. After Docker images are built, there is **no internet access**.

## Rules

- All assets (fonts, icons, images, JS/CSS libraries) MUST be bundled locally — never loaded from CDNs or external URLs at runtime.
- Docker images must contain everything needed to run. No runtime downloads (`wget`, `curl`, `fetch` to external hosts).
- NPM dependencies must be installed at build time only.
- No external API calls at runtime (analytics, telemetry, error reporting, external auth providers).
- Database seeds/imports must be baked into the Docker image or mounted from a local volume.
- If a build-time step fetches from the internet, there MUST be a fallback to a local copy already in the image.

## Verification Checklist

When adding features, verify:

1. No `<link>`, `<script>`, or `<img>` tags pointing to external domains
2. No Google Fonts, CDN-hosted libraries, or remote stylesheets
3. No runtime `fetch()` / `XMLHttpRequest` to external hosts
4. No Docker `CMD` or `ENTRYPOINT` that downloads files
5. All static assets exist in the repo or are generated at build time
